{"commentCount":6,"lastActivityDate":"2013-11-20 21:18:42.96","ownerUserId":"63","body":"&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;em&gt;î&lt;/em&gt; instead of &lt;em&gt;ii&lt;/em&gt; is something that was once done, but nowadays that is not done anymore, at least on everyday usage. Between &lt;em&gt;olii&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;oli&lt;/em&gt;, I would expect the latter to be used more often than the former, at least because it requires you to  write less letters, and generally there is no confusion about what &lt;em&gt;oli&lt;/em&gt; means. (It would not be taken as plural of &lt;em&gt;olo&lt;/em&gt;, since that is not an Italian word.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Lo Zingarelli&lt;/em&gt; reports just two plural word for &lt;em&gt;olio&lt;/em&gt;: &lt;em&gt;oli&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;olii&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;","score":4,"creationDate":"2013-11-20 21:18:42.96","title":"","tags":"","postTypeId":2,"id":1327}
