ot; and &quot;mi&quot; might have different functions within the sentence.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;A me mi&quot; should be avoided in formal spoken and written Italian, unless - of course - it is required by the chosen register.&lt;/p&gt;","score":8,"creationDate":"2014-03-06 10:23:23.1","title":"","tags":"","postTypeId":2,"id":1744}
