{"commentCount":0,"lastActivityDate":"2014-03-06 14:06:13.42","ownerUserId":"8","body":"&lt;p&gt;A suffix is an element of a language that is added to the end of a word.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes a noun can be modified to express a particular quality (large, small, pretty, ugly) without using a qualifying adjective. These nouns are created by taking the root of the noun and adding a suffix such as &lt;em&gt;-ino, -one, -etto,&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;em&gt;-accio&lt;/em&gt;. Most common Italian nouns can be modified, but the gender and number of the suffix must agree with the noun. &lt;/p&gt;","score":0,"creationDate":"2014-03-06 14:06:13.42","title":"","tags":"","postTypeId":5,"id":1794}
